Sanchez was absolutely incredible in red, he was the beating heart and soul for Arsenal and him leaving was the start of this brand new banter era for the Gunners. Hazard was not the best player for Chelsea for the beginning of this decade, and only really came into his own at the end of the decade- and even then he had a far FAR better team around him, and the stats still point to Sanchez being a better more important player in his prime than Eden was. Give me some hate c'mon, tell me I'm wrong
